# nl-rag distilled facts — domain: 1896-baltimore-orioles-season
# one declarative sentence per line; load with:  neuron --db app.db import pack.facts --scope knowledge
[src:1896-baltimore-orioles-season/1876-chicago-white-stockings-season] The **1876 Chicago White Stockings season** was the fifth season of the Chicago White Stockings franchise, the first in the National League and the third at 23rd Street Grounds.
[src:1896-baltimore-orioles-season/1876-chicago-white-stockings-season] The White Stockings, as one of the founding members of the new National League, won the NL's initial championship during this season with a record of 52–14.
[src:1896-baltimore-orioles-season/1877-boston-red-caps-season] The **1877 Boston Red Caps season** was the seventh season of the franchise.
[src:1896-baltimore-orioles-season/1877-boston-red-caps-season] Arthur Soden became the new owner of the franchise, who won their first National League pennant.
[src:1896-baltimore-orioles-season/1878-boston-red-caps-season] The **1878 Boston Red Caps season** was the eighth season of the franchise.
[src:1896-baltimore-orioles-season/1878-boston-red-caps-season] The Red Caps won their second straight National League pennant.
[src:1896-baltimore-orioles-season/1879-providence-grays-season] The **1879 Providence Grays** won the National League title in only their second season in the league.
[src:1896-baltimore-orioles-season/1880-chicago-white-stockings-season] The **1880 Chicago White Stockings season** was the ninth season of the Chicago White Stockings franchise, the fifth in the National League and the third at Lakefront Park.
[src:1896-baltimore-orioles-season/1880-chicago-white-stockings-season] The White Stockings won the National League championship with a record of 67–17.
[src:1896-baltimore-orioles-season/1881-chicago-white-stockings-season] The **1881 Chicago White Stockings season** was the tenth season of the Chicago White Stockings franchise, the sixth in the National League and the fourth at Lakefront Park.
[src:1896-baltimore-orioles-season/1881-chicago-white-stockings-season] The White Stockings won the National League championship with a record of 56–28.
[src:1896-baltimore-orioles-season/1882-baltimore-orioles-season] The 19th century's version of the **Baltimore Orioles** were founded in 1882 as part of the new American Association.
[src:1896-baltimore-orioles-season/1882-baltimore-orioles-season] Owned by wealthy Harry Von der Horst, the Orioles finished the season in last place with only 19 wins.
[src:1896-baltimore-orioles-season/1896-baltimore-orioles-season] The **Baltimore Orioles** won their third straight National League pennant in 1896.
[src:1896-baltimore-orioles-season/1896-baltimore-orioles-season] After the season, they faced the Cleveland Spiders in the Temple Cup for the second year in a row.
[src:1896-baltimore-orioles-season/1896-baltimore-orioles-season] After losing 4 games to 1 in 1895, the Orioles swept the Spiders in four straight.
[src:1896-baltimore-orioles-season/1896-baltimore-orioles-season] The Orioles had now played in the Cup in each of its first three seasons, with this one being their first win.
